<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro definition #define mhd_assert(ignore) ((void)0) causes every mhd_assert(...) call (for example the call mhd_assert(NULL != password); in MHD_digest_auth_check3) to expand to a no-op expression. Those no-op operations are executed but have no effect; removing them would not change program behaviour. Therefore these invocations constitute dead code and violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
